Belgian 2011 Deficit May Be Below 3%, Deputy Premier Tells Echo

-- B y   E w a   K r u k o w s k a
-- 
2011-04-14T06:32:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/belgian-2011-deficit-may-be-below-3-deputy-premier-tells-echo.html
Belgian Deputy Prime Minister
Laurette Onkelinx said she is “almost sure” that the country’s
federal budget deficit will be below 3 percent of gross domestic
product in 2011, according to  L’Echo .  Onkelinx told the newspaper that  Belgium ’s fundamentals are
“good” and its economy is projected to grow 2.3 percent in
2012, with the deficit not exceeding 2.8 percent of GDP. She
said she “hoped” the country will have a slight surplus in
2015, according to L’Echo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ewa Krukowska in Brussels at 
 ekrukowska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  